<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">SDI for Soybeans</span>
            <h2>How Drip Changes Soybean Risk Management</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🫘</div>
                <h3>Critical Stage Insurance</h3>
                <p>A single week of water stress during R1 flowering can reduce yield by 8–15%. SDI gives growers the ability to guarantee soil moisture adequacy during this window regardless of summer rainfall patterns.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🧪</div>
                <h3>Sulfur &amp; Potassium Fertigation</h3>
                <p>Soybeans fix their own nitrogen but have high potassium and sulfur demands. SDI fertigation delivers K and S to the root zone at pod fill — the stage where these nutrients have the highest yield impact.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌿</div>
                <h3>Improved Nodulation</h3>
                <p>Consistent soil moisture improves rhizobium nodulation activity and N-fixation efficiency. SDI growers typically see 10–20% higher nodule counts vs. rain-fed or sprinkler-irrigated fields.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌡️</div>
                <h3>Canopy Temperature Management</h3>
                <p>Soil evaporation from surface irrigation increases canopy humidity and disease pressure. SDI's minimal soil surface wetting reduces white mold and sudden death syndrome risk in susceptible environments.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">📏</div>
                <h3>Consistent Stand Density</h3>
                <p>SDI soil moisture at seeding prevents crusting and improves emergence uniformity — especially valuable in fields with variable soil texture where surface irrigation creates wet/dry inconsistencies.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-card">
                <div class="highlight-card-icon">📊</div>
                <h3>Case Study: Iowa Corridor</h3>
                <p>A 600-acre soybean SDI installation in central Iowa averaged 72 bu/acre over 3 seasons vs. 63 bu/acre on adjacent rainfed check strips — a 14% yield advantage with zero fertilizer rate changes.</p>
                <a href="/growers-stories" class="btn-primary-sm" style="margin-top:16px;">Read More →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

